# Chargeback Management Framework

## Overview

Chargebacks occur when retailers apply financial penalties due to operational non-compliance or shipment errors. These deductions are typically applied to invoices and can reduce revenue if not managed effectively.

Wholesale operations teams play a key role in preventing and resolving chargebacks through strong process controls and operational coordination.

---

## Common Causes of Chargebacks

Chargebacks most frequently occur due to:

• routing guide violations  
• late shipments  
• incorrect labeling  
• carton or pallet compliance issues  
• inaccurate invoices  
• missing shipment documentation  

Identifying the root cause helps organizations reduce repeat issues.

---

## Operational Impact

Chargebacks can impact the organization in several ways:

• lost revenue  
• increased operational workload  
• strained retailer relationships  
• reduced operational efficiency  

Monitoring chargeback trends allows organizations to improve operational processes.

---

## Chargeback Management Process

A structured chargeback process typically includes:

1. Chargeback identification  
2. Validation of retailer deduction  
3. Root cause analysis  
4. Internal investigation  
5. dispute submission if applicable  
6. operational correction  

This process ensures chargebacks are handled consistently.

---

## Prevention Strategies

Operations teams reduce chargebacks by:

• enforcing routing guide compliance  
• validating order data before shipment  
• ensuring proper labeling and documentation  
• improving shipment scheduling accuracy  

Prevention is significantly more effective than post-incident correction.

---

## Operational Monitoring

Operations teams should track chargeback metrics such as:

• chargeback frequency  
• chargeback dollar value  
• root cause category  
• retailer-specific trends  

These insights support continuous operational improvement.

---

## Final Note

Chargeback management is both a financial and operational responsibility. Strong operational discipline reduces retailer penalties and helps protect profitability in wholesale environments.
